 to include agent guidance, specifically setting system properties for native test runtime arguments for Netty 4.2.x. The question implies that proper environment and system property setups are essential for tests before we can reach meaningful coverage.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Investigating Netty and Java**\\n\\nI'm looking into Netty documentation regarding its compatibility with Java 24 and any unsafe memory access issues. I need to inspect the property names in Netty's PlatformDependent and figure out how they relate to Java's sun.misc.Unsafe. While searching online, I notice that I may not find many sources. I might want to consider downloading relevant documents to have the information readily available for my investigation. It seems like there's a lot to unravel!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_xj3emeQEO9Qf1Be8kZkWDEdZ|fc_0a7f7113e6d13d7d016a3ed075841c8197b754f713368c3509", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "find ~/.gradle/caches/modules-2/files-2.1/io.netty/netty-common/4.2.2.Final -type f -name '*.jar' -print"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1022, "output": 636, "cacheRead": 22528, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 24186, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1782501480032, "responseId": "resp_0a7f7113e6d13d7d016a3ed068832481978001ed2d9c583bbe"}}
